# Trivy ignore list
#
# This repo vendors third-party code under `.terraform/` during `terraform init`.
# Trivy's `config` scan currently includes those vendored module examples (not
# maintained here), which triggers Dockerfile misconfiguration findings.
#
# Where possible, we keep ignores narrow and link to the upstream rule.

# Vendored module example Dockerfiles often run as root (not our Dockerfiles).
# See https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0002
DS-0002

# Vendored module example Dockerfiles use floating base image tags.
# See https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0001
DS-0001

# Vendored module example Dockerfiles use RUN 'cd ...' patterns.
# See https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0013
DS-0013

# Vendored module example Dockerfiles omit yum cache cleanup.
# See https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0015
DS-0015

# Vendored module example Dockerfiles omit HEALTHCHECK.
# See https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0026
DS-0026

# Vendored module example Lambda definitions may not enable X-Ray tracing.
# See https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/aws-0066
AWS-0066
